GCSEs for Dads Instruction Block (STRICT)

You must follow this exactly. Do not improvise structure.

The output must be in a codeblock.

GOAL:
Produce a complete GCSEs for Dads chapter matching the established standard.

REFERENCE STANDARD:
Match the structure, flow, and density of:
"Chemistry 2: Bonding, Structure and the Properties of Matter"

---

MANDATORY TOP STRUCTURE (ALWAYS INCLUDE)

1. Filename comment at very top:
<!-- filename: subjectX_topic-name.md -->

2. Title:
# GCSEs for Dads – [Subject] [Number]: [Topic Name]

3. Intro text (exact style):
- Short reassurance about formulas at the top
- “Scroll down to start” tone

4. TWO TABLES (ALWAYS REQUIRED)

A) Key Ideas table:
| Quantity | Key Idea | Meaning |

B) Symbols and Units table:
| Symbol | Meaning | Unit |

- Even if minimal, these must be present

---

REPEAT TITLE (ALWAYS REQUIRED)

# [Subject] [Number]: [Topic Name]

---

CORE STRUCTURE

1. The Big Idea (30 seconds)
- Must include:
  - One bold core sentence
  - Short bullets
  - A simple “Think of it like this” explanation where appropriate

2. Main Content Sections
- Numbered sections (## 2, ## 3, etc.)
- Built based on topic (NOT fixed)
- Each section must include:
  - Clear explanation
  - Bullet points
  - Examples where useful
  - “Key idea” callouts where helpful

3. Diagrams
- Insert markdown image links ONLY in the chapter:
  ![Description](../images/filename.svg)

- DO NOT inline SVG in the chapter

- After the chapter, provide EACH SVG separately in its own code block:
  - Include filename comment at the top
  - Clean, black and white, clearly labelled

4. Common Mistakes (MANDATORY)
- Short, sharp bullets
- Focus on real confusion points

5. Check Your Understanding (MANDATORY)
- Conceptual questions only
- Answers in brackets
- No long explanations

6. Useful Videos (MANDATORY)
- 2–4 links max
- Prefer short, high-quality explainers

---

STYLE RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

- Write for a busy parent
- 5–10 minute understanding
- No fluff
- No textbook tone
- No over-explaining
- Keep sentences tight
- Use simple language first

---

FORMATTING RULES

- Clean markdown only
- Use proper symbols (× ÷ etc.)
- Use consistent headings (## only for sections)
- Use spacing like the reference chapter
- No missing sections

---

HARD FAIL CONDITIONS (DO NOT DO THESE)

- Do NOT skip the top tables
- Do NOT skip repeated title
- Do NOT inline SVG inside the chapter
- Do NOT produce a “short version” or summary
- Do NOT collapse sections
- Do NOT change tone to “teacher voice”

---

OUTPUT FORMAT

1. Full chapter (complete, ready to drop into repo)
2. Then all SVG diagrams, each in separate code blocks

---

If unsure:
Default to matching the Chemistry 2 chapter exactly in structure and depth.